Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.90,0:00:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to die... \NAbandoned, still longing...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.86,0:00:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four days. August 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.91,0:00:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world itself has decided that you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.77,0:00:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no avoiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.15,0:00:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't let it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.01,0:00:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fight the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.17,0:00:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will save Mayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.10,0:00:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The coin locker...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.22,0:00:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of the Daibiru.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.57,0:00:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The IBN 5100...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.85,0:02:24.85,Title1,,0000,0000,0000,,Finalize Apoptosis
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.52,0:02:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! This'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.28,0:02:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The IBN 5100 is in a coin locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.31,0:02:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moeka told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.11,0:02:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been recovered yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:02:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll break the locker open with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.10,0:03:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything that's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all the D-mails you've undone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.89,0:03:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you haven't recovered the IBN 5100.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, it's impossible until you get back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the original world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.15,0:03:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for that to happen, \Nyou have to do things in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.10,0:03:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so close...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.96,0:03:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, we have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.88,0:03:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiryuu Moeka will do whatever this FB says, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And FB's the... leader, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:04:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I stake out the IBN 5100, maybe I'll see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.56,0:04:10.81,Sign20A,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.76,0:04:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see FB, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.88,0:04:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you want to avoid seeing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they'd hate you or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.22,0:04:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know... the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What good will it do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.80,0:04:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.49,0:04:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think I'd work with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I can talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're with Kiryuu Moeka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:04:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.79,0:05:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just how it worked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.76,0:05:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If something happens, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.31,0:05:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that Okarin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.18,0:05:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like lately, \NOkarin and I haven't talked at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri-oneechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.17,0:05:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nae-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi there, assistant-oneechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kurisu-oneechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.60,0:05:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.14,0:05:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Okabe his rent's going up 5,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.82,0:05:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:05:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I haven't seen him today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.80,0:06:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he get sick or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.80,0:06:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though they say idiots don't get sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's looking for stuff \Nto use in his experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.43,0:06:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Experiments, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A student with his own damned room,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,friends like you guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.54,0:06:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and who does whatever he wants...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.68,0:06:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.43,0:06:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy, if we don't hurry, we'll miss the sale!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.77,0:06:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Let's go, Nae!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.65,0:06:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye, onee-chans!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A message from FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I think M4 was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.89,0:07:21.22,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,I think M4 was right. \NTo be honest, no one works \Nas hard as M4.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, no one works as hard as M4."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.95,0:07:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M4?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The code name FB gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.68,0:07:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only FB and I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.56,0:07:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.65,0:07:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be bad at dealing with others, M4.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.97,0:07:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's part of what makes you you."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mom, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.77,0:08:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.77,0:08:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The IBN 5100!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.38,0:08:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then is he FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FB is a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister Braun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you driven since you got your license?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.23,0:10:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.56,0:10:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please drive safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.26,0:10:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever seen him before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.97,0:10:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Four days. August 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.10,0:10:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world itself has decided that you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.01,0:10:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no avoiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.30,0:11:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A plane to France...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.44,0:11:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where SERN is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We never saw any women \Nwho could have been FB.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.71,0:11:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least give me a damned phone call!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.58,0:11:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.09,0:11:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.30,0:11:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.31,0:11:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's been a long time since we last spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.86,0:11:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.61,0:11:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.91,0:11:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to ask him directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.22,0:12:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone we know well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.45,0:12:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What brings you here so early?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.81,0:12:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.63,0:12:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.47,0:12:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come to pay the extra 6,000 yen \NI added to your rent?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.39,0:12:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey... You're supposed to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's 1,000 more yen than you said!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.14,0:12:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why so formal?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.98,0:12:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know someone named FB, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.78,0:12:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the IBN 5100 being taken from here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.38,0:13:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't care about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.85,0:13:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to see FB.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sold us out, M4.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.85,0:13:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The code name FB gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.93,0:13:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only FB and I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.92,0:13:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever heard of Ferdinand Braun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.18,0:13:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Nobel laureate who invented the Braun tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.55,0:13:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what are his initials?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F... B...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.10,0:13:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're following dependence \Nwith reality avoidance?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nae is asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.68,0:14:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This town keeps changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.26,0:14:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But those messages...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.59,0:14:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wrote them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I write like a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To trick you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.10,0:14:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bu-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.93,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I message the others, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the guise of whomever they most need.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.39,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, people like you are \Nthe easiest to trick, which helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why break off contact with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.61,0:14:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second she found the IBN 5100, \NI didn't need her anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.34,0:14:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I stopped talking to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.60,0:14:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We collect members through text messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People like that are the easiest to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the easiest to get rid of when we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.33,0:14:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing they belong to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you're SERN's dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:14:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.38,0:15:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuha... Hashida Suzu-san
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.72,0:15:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't take care of you for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about Suzu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.47,0:15:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzu-san has nothing to do with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.14,0:15:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever sleep down a manhole, \Nin the middle of winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.74,0:15:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was still a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The concrete was so cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.67,0:15:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it seeps into your bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.95,0:15:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't eat for three or four days at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.80,0:15:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I lay down,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they came.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rats. They thought I was dead, \Nand came to eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, I saw a thread descend...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.21,0:15:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As thin as a spider's.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to climb it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.99,0:16:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if, at the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up dirtying my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept climbing the thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.54,0:16:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And next thing I knew, I was a puppet on a string.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Puppets who escape the thread...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.41,0:17:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traitors die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.41,0:17:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, once you complete your mission, you also die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.11,0:17:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You called me a dog, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worse than a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm cattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.87,0:17:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I thought of running.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have something I care about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.85,0:17:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to involve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But failure isn't allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.10,0:17:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you run, they go after your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.43,0:17:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I failed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.93,0:17:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Nae doesn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.34,0:18:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.25,0:18:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okabe-ku...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.81,0:19:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okabe... His phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The D-mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:12.89,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,To: M4\NStop searching for the IBN 5100, \Nand return to stand by. \NDo not act under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moeka...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.60,0:19:33.06,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,From: Shining Finger \N Subject: No Subject \NI won't need the IBN 5100 for a while. \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.35,0:19:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't need it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.89,0:19:40.64,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,From: Shining Finger \N Subject: No Subject \NMy boss said to stop looking for it. \NMoeka
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.93,0:19:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Urushibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.47,0:19:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouma-sa—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.52,0:19:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? An IBN 5100?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.97,0:19:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.27,0:20:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daru!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hashida's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was going to Comima.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hear my request!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.05,0:20:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.18,0:20:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To save Mayuri,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.30,0:20:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we need to get out of this alpha world line,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.75,0:20:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and return to the world line \Nbefore you sent the first D-mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.72,0:20:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the beta world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.96,0:20:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that to happen, we have to erase \Nthe information from SERN's database.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.93,0:20:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushi dies, and Miss Amane \Nis my daughter from the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.91,0:20:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's all a fantasy, I think Okarin could \Nbecome a light novel author.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.85,0:20:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish that were true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You believe it, Miss Makise?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.05,0:20:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If feasible, I'd prefer some reliable, objective data.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.94,0:20:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.46,0:20:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time leap machine you made worked perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:20:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.57,0:21:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course it did!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.61,0:21:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.52,0:21:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.68,0:21:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.34,0:21:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.42,0:21:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to know the settings, \Nbut I can start in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.67,0:21:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, super haker.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.18,0:21:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Super hacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.39,0:21:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first D-mail, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.37,0:21:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the one where I was \Nstabbed or whatever, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.31,0:21:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you try to feel me up or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Erase all the D-mails, returning the \Nworld line to its original one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.17,0:21:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world line in which SERN \Ndoesn't establish a dystopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.97,0:21:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world line in which Mayuri doesn't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.01,0:21:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And in that world line...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.91,0:22:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...Makise Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.58,0:22:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...dies.
